  "prompt": "So, can a sentence begin with the word \"so\"?",
  "response": "Yes, a sentence can begin with the word \"so.\" In informal writing and conversation, \"so\" is often used as a discourse marker to introduce a new topic, show a consequence, or summarize a previous discussion. For example, you might use it to transition from one idea to another or to highlight a logical conclusion. However, in more formal writing, it's generally recommended to use \"so\" more sparingly at the beginning of sentences, as it can make the text seem too conversational.",
